  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "HOulOOC/Ejk7I2z7PrULUsxeRB8=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:28.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "Prerequisites for running the Bee Reactor Adapter:\n\n- **Full Bee node** reachable from the browser. Chat requires full-node PSS + GSOC support \u2014 light nodes can send messages but not receive them.\n- **Mutable postage stamp** at depth 22+ (~7.7 GB capacity). Mutability is required so feed updates reuse bucket slots rather than re-paying for storage.\n- **Ethereum wallet** (MetaMask or any Web3 wallet) for Renown login and for deriving the encryption key.\n- **Open inbound ports** `1634` (TCP) and `1635` (WSS) for libp2p WebSocket transport used by peer-to-peer chat.\n\nIf chat cannot start, the chat panel surfaces a requirements screen showing the exact Bee config keys needed. Wallet signatures double as both authentication and the seed for device-portable decryption keys, which is what enables cross-device recovery from just a wallet.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:28.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:28.000Z"
    }
  },
